My invitation to you in 2021 is to ask this question to your friends, colleagues, family and even strangers. And if you are convinced “Fine” is an inadequate answer, don’t be shy to probe, cajole and use any means necessary to extract a truthful response. 
I fell prey to the word "Fine" once and it nearly cost me my sanity. In September 2020, I was abducted and robbed at gunpoint. The ordeal lasted just a few hours but the trauma inflicted will probably stay with me for a lifetime. I was physically unharmed. But as I came to learn, sometimes the invisible wounds are more painful than physical ones. 



