I started seeing a counsellor a few days after the incident. And it was only after I sincerely answered her question, "How are you?" after weeks of counselling that she recommended I see a psychiatrist.
I was not okay but felt an imagined pressure to display strength even when I was feeling like the weight of the world was sitting on my shoulders. 
Post-traumatic stress disorder
The psychiatrist diagnosed me with post-traumatic stress disorder, a mental health condition triggered by a terrifying event. I was relieved to finally have a label for the flashbacks, anxiety attacks, stress, irritability and insomnia that had plagued me for weeks on end. 



